      "id": "spine_biology_l4_bacterial_cell_envelope",
      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_prokaryotic_cell_structure",
      "content": {
        "title": "Bacterial Cell Envelope",
        "definition": "Layered structure comprising plasma membrane, peptidoglycan cell wall, and in gram-negative bacteria an outer membrane with lipopolysaccharide.",
        "summary": "The cell envelope provides shape, osmotic protection, and a permeability barrier. Gram stain distinguishes thick peptidoglycan (gram-positive) from thin peptidoglycan plus outer membrane (gram-negative)."
      },
