      "content": {
        "title": "Gram Stain and Cell Wall Properties",
        "definition": "Differential staining based on peptidoglycan thickness and lipid content distinguishing gram-positive (purple) from gram-negative (pink) bacteria.",
        "summary": "Crystal violet retention in thick peptidoglycan defines gram-positive organisms. Outer membrane of gram-negatives prevents dye retention after alcohol decolorization."
