      "id": "spine_biology_l4_prokaryotic_cell_envelope",
      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_prokaryotic_cell_structure",
      "content": {
        "title": "Prokaryotic Cell Envelope (Wall and Membrane)",
        "definition": "Peptidoglycan cell wall surrounding the plasma membrane in bacteria, with gram-positive thick single layer and gram-negative thin wall plus outer membrane.",
        "summary": "The envelope provides osmotic protection and antibiotic targets. Lysozyme cleaves peptidoglycan; beta-lactams inhibit cross-linking."
      },
