      "resolution_level": 4,
      "anchor_concept_id": "spine_biology_l3_prokaryotic_cell_structure",
      "content": {
        "title": "Prokaryotic Genome and Plasmids",
        "definition": "Circular double-stranded DNA chromosome in the nucleoid region plus optional small extrachromosomal plasmids carrying accessory genes such as antibiotic resistance.",
        "summary": "Prokaryotic genomes are compact with little noncoding DNA. Plasmids enable horizontal gene transfer and rapid adaptation."
      },
